_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟠 Major_ | _⚡ Quick win_

**Handle thrown HTTP/JSON errors to avoid full sync failure.**

A single thrown fetch/json error currently rejects the whole read path (including enrichment lanes), despite the intended graceful degradation behavior.

<details>
<summary>Suggested fix</summary>

```diff
-	const searchRes = await http(searchUrl, { headers });
+	let searchRes: HttpResponse;
+	try {
+		searchRes = await http(searchUrl, { headers });
+	} catch {
+		return empty;
+	}
 ...
-	const items = parseSearchItems(await searchRes.json());
+	let items: SearchItem[] = [];
+	try {
+		items = parseSearchItems(await searchRes.json());
+	} catch {
+		return empty;
+	}
 ...
 	const { results, rateLimited } = await runConcurrent(
 		detailUrls,
 		concurrency,
 		async ({ url }) => {
-			const res = await http(url, { headers });
+			let res: HttpResponse;
+			try {
+				res = await http(url, { headers });
+			} catch {
+				return null;
+			}
 			if (isRateLimited(res)) {
 				debugLog({ kind: "rate_limit_hit", phase: "enrichment", url });
 				return "rate_limited" as const;
 			}
 			if (!res.ok) return null;
-			return parsePRDetail(await res.json());
+			try {
+				return parsePRDetail(await res.json());
+			} catch {
+				return null;
+			}
 		},
 	);
```
</details>




Also applies to: 269-280

<details>
<summary>🤖 Prompt for AI Agents</summary>

```
Verify each finding against current code. Fix only still-valid issues, skip the
rest with a brief reason, keep changes minimal, and validate.

In `@packages/engine/src/sources/github.ts` around lines 241 - 250, The fetch and
JSON parsing steps around http(searchUrl, { headers }) and
parseSearchItems(await searchRes.json()) can throw and currently bubble up; wrap
both the HTTP call and the JSON parsing in a try/catch so thrown errors are
caught and the function returns the graceful fallback (the existing empty-like
response with rateLimitHit/other flags) instead of crashing the whole sync;
specifically, in the block that uses searchUrl/searchRes/items and the similar
block at the other location (lines 269-280 equivalent) catch errors from
http(...) and from searchRes.json(), debugLog the error (including context like
searchUrl and phase), and return the same empty response (or { ...empty,
fetchError: true }) so enrichment lanes can continue.
```

</details>

